About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

Todayâ€™s recipe is Diwali faral shankarpali using 1 kilo maida. It turns out nice, crispy and flaky. Diwali faral is incomplete without shankarpali. We already have seen different recipes if shankarpali. This is full proof recipe the proportion used is just perfect. It is a very easy and simple recipe. You can make it within no time. Besides, I am sharing few tips to make perfect shankarpali. This is a popular Marathi recipe. Also it can be a good tea time snack. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.

Ingredients:
â€¢ 1 cup Milk
â€¢ 1 cup Sugar
â€¢ 1 cup Ghee
â€¢ 7 cups / 1 kilo Maida
â€¢ Oil for frying

Method:
â€¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and add milk and sugar. 
â€¢ Heat it up together until sugar is dissolved. 
â€¢ When sugar is dissolved and the mixture begins to boil, turn off the gas and add ghee. 
â€¢ Melt ghee before measuring. Make sure you donâ€™t use thick ghee. 
â€¢ Mix well and base for shankarpali is ready. 
â€¢ Transfer the base into the maida and mix in with the help of ladle. 
â€¢ Knead the mixture into dough. 
â€¢ Make small portions of the dough. Keep the leftover dough covered with a wet cloth.
â€¢ Take one portion and roll it into a thick chapati. The thickness of the chapati should be about 1 
  cm. 
â€¢ Cut off the edges and roll the chapati little more if you want. 
â€¢ Cut shankarpali into size and shape you want and take them out into a dish. 
â€¢ Rolled out shankarpali should not dry out. 
â€¢ Heat up oil on high heat for about 5 minutes and reduce the heat to low. 
â€¢ Drop shankarpali into hot oil and fry it well for at least 3-4 minutes. 
â€¢ If oil is hot enough and still shankarpali dissolves in oil, then add a little more maida into the 
  dough. Add a little milk and knead the dough again. Roll out shankarpali and fry. It wonâ€™t dissolve. 
â€¢ When shankarpali gets nice golden color from all sides, take it out, drain excess oil and transfer it 
  into a dish. Shankarpali is ready.
â€¢ You can store them in an air tight container when they cool down completely. They have shelf life 
  of about 1 month.

Todayâ€™s recipe is Diwali faral shankarpali using 1 kilo maida. It turns out nice, crispy and flaky. Diwali faral is incomplete without shankarpali. We already have seen different recipes if shankarpali. This is full proof recipe the proportion used is just perfect. It is a very easy and simple recipe. You can make it within no time. Besides, I am sharing few tips to make perfect shankarpali. This is a popular Marathi recipe. Also it can be a good tea time snack. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.

Ingredients:
â€¢ 1 cup Milk
â€¢ 1 cup Sugar
â€¢ 1 cup Ghee
â€¢ 7 cups / 1 kilo Maida
â€¢ Oil for frying

Method:
â€¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and add milk and sugar. 
â€¢ Heat it up together until sugar is dissolved. 
â€¢ When sugar is dissolved and the mixture begins to boil, turn off the gas and add ghee. 
â€¢ Melt ghee before measuring. Make sure you donâ€™t use thick ghee. 
â€¢ Mix well and base for shankarpali is ready. 
â€¢ Transfer the base into the maida and mix in with the help of ladle. 
â€¢ Knead the mixture into dough. 
â€¢ Make small portions of the dough. Keep the leftover dough covered with a wet cloth.
â€¢ Take one portion and roll it into a thick chapati. The thickness of the chapati should be about 1 
  cm. 
â€¢ Cut off the edges and roll the chapati little more if you want. 
â€¢ Cut shankarpali into size and shape you want and take them out into a dish. 
â€¢ Rolled out shankarpali should not dry out. 
â€¢ Heat up oil on high heat for about 5 minutes and reduce the heat to low. 
â€¢ Drop shankarpali into hot oil and fry it well for at least 3-4 minutes. 
â€¢ If oil is hot enough and still shankarpali dissolves in oil, then add a little more maida into the 
  dough. Add a little milk and knead the dough again. Roll out shankarpali and fry. It wonâ€™t dissolve. 
â€¢ When shankarpali gets nice golden color from all sides, take it out, drain excess oil and transfer it 
  into a dish. Shankarpali is ready.
â€¢ You can store them in an air tight container when they cool down completely. They have shelf life 
  of about 1 month.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalalâ€™s Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in 'Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

India beat South Africa by 243 runs, in Kolkata

In the grand stage of the ICC World Cup 2023, Team India left an indelible mark with an awe-inspiring victory against South Africa. This thrilling match was more than just a cricket encounter; it was a breathtaking saga of determination, skill, and unwavering spirit that captured the hearts of millions of fans around the world.

From the very first ball, it was evident that the contest was destined to be extraordinary. South Africa, a formidable opponent, was ready to give their all, but Team India, under the captaincy of Rohit Sharma, was equally prepared to rise to the occasion. The world watched with bated breath as two cricketing giants clashed on the field.
#viratkohli #viratbirthday #cricket #viratcentury 

With the help of some brilliant and impactful play from Virat Kohli, Shreyas Iyer, Rohit Sharma, Shubhman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav and Ravindra Jadeja, India have given South Africa a target of 327 runs. King Kohli gifted himself his 49th ODI century today in Kolkata.

Ingredients:
Bhajani
â€¢ 2 1/2 cup / 500 gm Rice
â€¢ 1 cup / 200 gm Chana dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Moong dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Urad dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Poha
â€¢ 20 gm Coriander seeds
â€¢ 20 gm Cumin seeds
Chakali
â€¢ 3 cups Water
â€¢ 1/4 cup Oil
â€¢ 1 tsp Oil
â€¢ 1 tsp Red chili powder
â€¢ Salt to taste
â€¢ 1 tbsp Coriander powder
â€¢ 1 kilo Chakali bhajani
â€¢ 1 tsp Ajwain / Carom seeds
â€¢ 1 tsp white Sesame seeds
â€¢ Oil for frying

Method:
â€¢ Wipe the rice really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe chana dal really good with clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe moong dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe urad dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ You can wash and dry all these ingredients if you want. 
â€¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and roast rice really good. 
â€¢ The rice should be roasted well but the color should not change. 
â€¢ When the rice is roasted well take it out into a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast chana dal really good until it begins to get reddish color and take it out into 
  a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast moong dal well until it gets reddish color and take it out into a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast urad dal really good until it gets light golden color and take it out into a 
  dish. 
â€¢ Roast poha really good and transfer them into the dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast coriander seeds and cumin seeds together on low heat until nice aroma 
  begins to release from it and transfer it into the dish. 
â€¢ Mix everything well together and let it cool down. 
â€¢ Grind it from the mill. Make sure that it is ground after rice or jawar is ground and not after wheat. 
â€¢ Blend it into flour in mixer and sieve it through flour strainer. 
â€¢ Blend the leftover coarse flour in the strain again in blender and sieve it. Bhajani for chakali is 
  ready.
Chakali
â€¢ Heat up water in a pan and add oil. 
â€¢ Mix well and add red chili powder, salt, coriander powder. 
â€¢ Mix well and when the mixture boils really good, reduce the heat to low. 
â€¢ Add the bhajani flour and turn off the gas. 
â€¢ Add carom seeds, sesame seeds and mix everything well together quickly. 
â€¢ Transfer the ukad into a dish and knead dough. If needed use very little hot water. 
â€¢ Knead the ukad really good when it is still hot. The consistency of the dough should be stiff. 
â€¢ Take small portion from the dough and knead it really good again. 
â€¢ Make a smooth and even roll and transfer it into chakali machine. 
â€¢ Press the dough well and roll out chakali from it on a butter paper. 
â€¢ Seal both the ends of the chakali really good. 
â€¢You can use plastic sheet or dish in place of butter paper. 
â€¢ Heat up oil in a pan on medium to high heat for about 6-7 minutes and drop a small chakali in it. 
â€¢ If it is fried well, then the oil is hot enough. 
â€¢ Drop chakali into hot oil and fry well. 
â€¢ When the chakali begins to settle at the bottom, flip it over and fry well from other side too. 
â€¢ When chakali begins to settle at the bottom of the pan, it means it is fried well from both sides. 
â€¢ Take the chakali out, drain excess oil and transfer it into a dish. Chakali is ready.

Ingredients:
Bhajani
â€¢ 2 1/2 cup / 500 gm Rice
â€¢ 1 cup / 200 gm Chana dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Moong dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Urad dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Poha
â€¢ 20 gm Coriander seeds
â€¢ 20 gm Cumin seeds
Chakali
â€¢ 3 cups Water
â€¢ 1/4 cup Oil
â€¢ 1 tsp Oil
â€¢ 1 tsp Red chili powder
â€¢ Salt to taste
â€¢ 1 tbsp Coriander powder
â€¢ 1 kilo Chakali bhajani
â€¢ 1 tsp Ajwain / Carom seeds
â€¢ 1 tsp white Sesame seeds
â€¢ Oil for frying

Method:
â€¢ Wipe the rice really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe chana dal really good with clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe moong dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe urad dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ You can wash and dry all these ingredients if you want. 
â€¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and roast rice really good. 
â€¢ The rice should be roasted well but the color should not change. 
â€¢ When the rice is roasted well take it out into a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast chana dal really good until it begins to get reddish color and take it out into 
  a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast moong dal well until it gets reddish color and take it out into a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast urad dal really good until it gets light golden color and take it out into a 
  dish. 
â€¢ Roast poha really good and transfer them into the dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast coriander seeds and cumin seeds together on low heat until nice aroma 
  begins to release from it and transfer it into the dish. 
â€¢ Mix everything well together and let it cool down. 
â€¢ Grind it from the mill. Make sure that it is ground after rice or jawar is ground and not after wheat. 
â€¢ Blend it into flour in mixer and sieve it through flour strainer. 
â€¢ Blend the leftover coarse flour in the strain again in blender and sieve it. Bhajani for chakali is 
  ready.
Chakali
â€¢ Heat up water in a pan and add oil. 
â€¢ Mix well and add red chili powder, salt, coriander powder. 
â€¢ Mix well and when the mixture boils really good, reduce the heat to low. 
â€¢ Add the bhajani flour and turn off the gas. 
â€¢ Add carom seeds, sesame seeds and mix everything well together quickly. 
â€¢ Transfer the ukad into a dish and knead dough. If needed use very little hot water. 
â€¢ Knead the ukad really good when it is still hot. The consistency of the dough should be stiff. 
â€¢ Take small portion from the dough and knead it really good again. 
â€¢ Make a smooth and even roll and transfer it into chakali machine. 
â€¢ Press the dough well and roll out chakali from it on a butter paper. 
â€¢ Seal both the ends of the chakali really good. 
â€¢You can use plastic sheet or dish in place of butter paper. 
â€¢ Heat up oil in a pan on medium to high heat for about 6-7 minutes and drop a small chakali in it. 
â€¢ If it is fried well, then the oil is hot enough. 
â€¢ Drop chakali into hot oil and fry well. 
â€¢ When the chakali begins to settle at the bottom, flip it over and fry well from other side too. 
â€¢ When chakali begins to settle at the bottom of the pan, it means it is fried well from both sides. 
â€¢ Take the chakali out, drain excess oil and transfer it into a dish. Chakali is ready.

Episode 3920: Moon Residential Program
--------------------------------------------------------
Bawri enters Gada Shop and discusses the popular video about acquiring a lunar plot. Bagha discusses to Jetha the vitality of emerging technology. Bagha discusses cryptocurrency and bitcoins. Jetha is enthusiastic about understanding the significance of NFT and the metaverse. All of these new advances in technology urge Jetha to contact the MRP (Moon Residential Programme) management and reserve a site. Jetha finally appears at the MRP's local Mumbai office to buy Babita's land. Watch the episode to find out how Jetha closes the deal with Mr. Chand, the manager.

snippet.title: Milk Sweet recipe in Tamil | Kalakand Recipe in Tamil
snippet.description:
In this video we will see how to make milk sweet recipe in tamil. This milk sweet / Kalakand is made by curdling milk with some lemon juice which creates some precipitated milk curds and these are then caramelized under heat to impart that rich, chewy, caramel taste. Compared to the regular milk sweet, this version has a lot more texture and chewiness to it. This Kalakand recipe is popular during festival time and can be topped with some nuts.
#milksweetrecipe #milksweetrecipeintamil #kalakandrecipe 

Friends, please do try this milk sweet recipe at home and share it with your friends and family. Also, please do share your feedback about the recipe in the comments below. All the best and happy cooking! 

Ingredients:
2 Liter full fat Milk (8 cup)
1 cup Sugar(200g) can be increased to 1.25 cup
juice of half Lemon
2+2 tbsp Ghee
pinch of Cardamom powder

snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Maa Nahi Saas Hoon Main Episode 03 - [Eng Sub] - Hammad Shoaib - Sumbul Iqbal - Farhan Ally Agha - 5th November 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

This story revolves around Mehreen and her daughter Areej, who was born after years of prayers. Prior to her birth, Mehreen and her husband had been caring for Salman, Areej's cousin. However, a tragedy struck, separating Areej from her family. Afterwards, Mehreen decided to raise Salman as her own son.
Years later, Salman crosses paths with Urooj, a beautiful and fearless girl, the daughter of school teacher Shoaib and his wife Naseem. Initially resistant to Salman's advances, Urooj eventually falls in love with him. Unbeknownst to Salman and his family, Urooj is none other than Areej, Mehreen's long-lost daughter.
Will Urooj discover the truth about her identity? How will the family come to know that Urooj is Mehreenâ€™s long-lost daughter, Areej? How will Urooj react when she gets to know that Mehreen is her real mother? What impact will Uroojâ€™s identity have on Salman? Will Mehreen accept Urooj as her daughter? Will Uroojâ€™s true identity pose a threat to her relationship with Salman?

This story revolves around Mehreen and her daughter Areej, who was born after years of prayers. Prior to her birth, Mehreen and her husband had been caring for Salman, Areej's cousin. However, a tragedy struck, separating Areej from her family. Afterwards, Mehreen decided to raise Salman as her own son.
Years later, Salman crosses paths with Urooj, a beautiful and fearless girl, the daughter of school teacher Shoaib and his wife Naseem. Initially resistant to Salman's advances, Urooj eventually falls in love with him. Unbeknownst to Salman and his family, Urooj is none other than Areej, Mehreen's long-lost daughter.
Will Urooj discover the truth about her identity? How will the family come to know that Urooj is Mehreenâ€™s long-lost daughter, Areej? How will Urooj react when she gets to know that Mehreen is her real mother? What impact will Uroojâ€™s identity have on Salman? Will Mehreen accept Urooj as her daughter? About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalalâ€™s Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in 'Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

Besan Ladu Recipe

snippet.title: The Beatles - Now And Then (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Now and Then's eventful journey to fruition took place over five decades and is the product of conversations and collaborations between the four Beatles that go on to this day. The long mythologised John Lennon demo was first worked on in February 1995 by Paul, George and Ringo as part of The Beatles Anthology project but it remained unfinished, partly because of the impossible technological challenges involved in working with the vocal John had recorded on tape in the 1970s. For years it looked like the song could never be completed. But in 2022 there was a stroke of serendipity. A software system developed by Peter Jackson and his team, used throughout the production of the documentary series Get Back, finally opened the way for the uncoupling of Johnâ€™s vocal from his piano part. As a result, the original recording could be brought to life and worked on anew with contributions from all four Beatles. This remarkable story of musical archaeology reflects The Beatlesâ€™ endless creative curiosity and shared fascination with technology. It marks the completion of the last recording that John, Paul and George and Ringo will get to make together and celebrates the legacy of the foremost and most influential band in popular music history.

Video Director: Peter Jackson
Video Producers: Peter Jackson, Clare Olssen, Jonathan Clyde
Audio Producers: Paul McCartney and Giles Martin
Production Company: WingNut Films Productions Ltd

snippet.title: The Fall Guy | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
The Stuntman becomes the hero. #TheFallGuyMovie only in theaters March 1.

------

Heâ€™s a stuntman, and like everyone in the stunt community, he gets blown up, shot, crashed, thrown through windows and dropped from the highest of heights, all for our entertainment. And now, fresh off an almost career-ending accident, this working-class hero has to track down a missing movie star, solve a conspiracy and try to win back the love of his life while still doing his day job. What could possibly go right? 

From real life stunt man and director David Leitch, the blockbuster director of Bullet Train, Deadpool 2, Atomic Blonde and Fast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw and the producer of John Wick, Nobody and Violent Night, comes his most personal film yet. A new hilarious, hard-driving, all-star apex-action thriller and love letter to action movies and the hard-working and under-appreciated crew of people who make them: The Fall Guy. 

OscarÂ® nominee Ryan Gosling (Barbie, La La Land, Drive) stars as Colt Seavers, a battle-scarred stuntman who, having left the business a year earlier to focus on both his physical and mental health, is drafted back into service when the star of a mega-budget studio movieâ€”being directed by his ex, Jody Moreno, played by Golden Globe winner Emily Blunt (Oppenheimer, A Quiet Place films, Sicario)â€”goes missing.

While the filmâ€™s ruthless producer (Emmy winner Hannah Waddingham; Ted Lasso), maneuvers to keep the disappearance of star Tom Ryder (Golden Globe winner Aaron Taylor-Johnson; Bullet Train) a secret from the studio and the media, Colt performs the filmâ€™s most outrageous stunts while trying (with limited success) to charm his way back into Jodyâ€™s good graces. But as the mystery around the missing star deepens, Colt will find himself ensnared in a sinister, criminal plot that will push him to the edge of a fall more dangerous than any stunt.

Inspired by the hit 1980s TV series, The Fall Guy also stars Winston Duke (Black Panther franchise) and Academy AwardÂ® nominee Stephanie Hsu (Everything Everywhere All at Once). 

From a screenplay by Hobbs & Shaw screenwriter Drew Pearce, The Fall Guy is produced by Kelly McCormick (Bullet Train, Nobody, Atomic Blonde) and David Leitch for their company 87North, and by Ryan Gosling and by Guymon Casady (Game of Thrones, Steve Jobs and executive producer of the upcoming series Ripley) for Entertainment 360. The film is executive produced by Drew Pearce, Entertainment 360â€™s Geoff Shaevitz and the creator of the original Fall Guy television series, Glen A. Larson.

OscarÂ® nominee Ryan Gosling (Barbie, La La Land, Drive) stars as Colt Seavers, a battle-scarred stuntman who, having left the business a year earlier to focus on both his physical and mental health, is drafted back into service when the star of a mega-budget studio movieâ€”being directed by his ex, Jody Moreno, played by Golden Globe winner Emily Blunt (Oppenheimer, A Quiet Place films, Sicario)â€”goes missing.

While the filmâ€™s ruthless producer (Emmy winner Hannah Waddingham; Ted Lasso), maneuvers to keep the disappearance of star Tom Ryder (Golden Globe winner Aaron Taylor-Johnson; Bullet Train) a secret from the studio and the media, Colt performs the filmâ€™s most outrageous stunts while trying (with limited success) to charm his way back into Jodyâ€™s good graces. But as the mystery around the missing star deepens, Colt will find himself ensnared in a sinister, criminal plot that will push him to the edge of a fall more dangerous than any stunt.

Inspired by the hit 1980s TV series, The Fall Guy also stars Winston Duke (Black Panther franchise) and Academy AwardÂ® nominee Stephanie Hsu (Everything Everywhere All at Once). 

From a screenplay by Hobbs & Shaw screenwriter Drew Pearce, The Fall Guy is produced by Kelly McCormick (Bullet Train, Nobody, Atomic Blonde) and David Leitch for their company 87North, and by Ryan Gosling and by Guymon Casady (Game of Thrones, Steve Jobs and executive producer of the upcoming series Ripley) for Entertainment 360. The film is executive produced by Drew Pearce, Entertainment 360â€™s Geoff Shaevitz and the creator of the original Fall Guy television series, Glen A. Larson.
